# ✨ Effect Manager (`al_effect_manager.gd`)

## Overview

The **Effect Manager** is the central authority for all gameplay effects within the framework.

All effects in the game flow through this system. No standalone effects operate outside of the manager.

This includes:

* ⚔️ Combat effects
* 🧪 Consumable effects
* 🛡️ Equipment effects
* 🔥 Damage over Time (DOT)
* 💚 Healing over Time (HOT)
* 📈 Stat modifiers
* 🎯 Critical / hit effects
* 💀 Revival effects
* 🌀 Crowd control effects
* 🌍 Difficulty scaling effects

Difficulty is implemented as a **passive effect**, allowing world modifiers and gameplay scaling to use the same effect pipeline as player and enemy modifiers.

---

# 🧠 Core Responsibilities

The Effect Manager provides:

* Centralized effect application
* Target resolution
* Stat modifier routing
* Temporary effect tracking
* Effect expiration
* Damage/healing ticks
* Effect cleanup
* Combat event logging

All effect sources use the same application pipeline regardless of origin.

